f=Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md · p=Reference MCP marketplace tool integrated Engineering department. tool entry includes: what does, which agents use it, setup requirements, integration rationale. tools run under Security Charter (Rail plan-lock, Rail sandbox+egress). · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| Agent \| Tools \| Primary Use \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\|-------\|-------\|-------------\| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **dev** \| Ponytail \| Code review over-engineering detection, minimal-code principle enforcement \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **ops** \| — \| (No MCP tools assigned — ops monitors tools, doesn't run them in prod) \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **cypher** \| Browserbase, Firecrawl, Scrapling \| Reconnaissance, attack surface discovery, stealth scraping \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **aegis** \| Browserbase \| Security surface testing (CSP, CORS, cookies), visual regression \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **axiom** \| Ponytail \| Algorithm simplicity enforcement, "use stdlib first" before custom implementation \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **rank** \| Firecrawl, Crawl4AI, Scrapling, Website Cloner \| SEO competitive analysis, content extraction, SERP monitoring \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **quinn** \| Browserbase \| Browser-based E2E testing, visual regression, screenshot comparison \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **dana** \| Firecrawl, Crawl4AI, Scrapling \| Data ingestion pipelines, RAG content extraction, structured web data \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **raj** \| — \| (No MCP tools — API design doesn't need web scraping/browser automation) \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **mia** \| Browserbase, Website Cloner, awesome-design-md \| UI testing, design extraction, brand-consistent UI generation \| · h2:Agent Coverage Map=\| **nova** \| Browserbase \| Mobile web testing via cloud browsers, app store screenshot automation \|